## Transition Criteria

Before proceeding to the next phase, participants should demonstrate:

- Completion of all module exercises
- Understanding of key concepts through checkpoint assessments
- Ability to apply tools and methods to their capstone project

## Quality Checkpoints

{% if phaseOrder == "1" %}
- [ ] Project charter approved by sponsor
- [ ] MGPP (Multigeneration Plan) documented
- [ ] Risk management plan established
- [ ] Team roles and communication plan defined
- [ ] CTQ flowdowns completed
{% elif phaseOrder == "2" %}
- [ ] Voice of Customer captured and analyzed
- [ ] QFD (House of Quality) completed
- [ ] Metrics and scorecards established
- [ ] Measurement system analysis validated
- [ ] Process capability assessed
{% elif phaseOrder == "3" %}
- [ ] Concept generation using TRIZ completed
- [ ] Pugh concept selection documented
- [ ] Tolerance analysis performed
- [ ] Monte Carlo simulation completed
- [ ] Hypothesis testing validated
{% elif phaseOrder == "4" %}
- [ ] ANOVA results documented
- [ ] DOE (full-factorial and fractional) completed
- [ ] RSM model validated
- [ ] Reliability targets verified
- [ ] Robust design parameters optimized
{% elif phaseOrder == "5" %}
- [ ] Prototype testing completed
- [ ] Pilot results validated
- [ ] SPC charts established
- [ ] Implementation plan approved
- [ ] Capstone project presented
{% endif %}

